honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl

Class NetworkWirelessSettings_DPL

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterData_DPL
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterState_DPL
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.NetworkWirelessSettings_DPL
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class NetworkWirelessSettings_DPL
extends PrinterState_DPL
    This class handles the network wireless settings data from the [STX]KcQQQ query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    1Enable Static DNS
    2Preferred DNS Server
    3Secondary DNS Server
    4DNS Suffix
    20Inactive Timeout
    21IP Address method
    22Active IP Address
    23Active Subnet Mask
    24Active Gateway Address
    25Printer DNS name
    26Register to DNS
    27Use DNS Suffix
    28UDP Port
    29TCP Port
    30Enable Connection Status
    31DHCP User Class Option
    32Static IP Address
    33Static Subnet Mask
    34Static Gateway
    35LPD Port
    36LPD Enable
    40Network Type
    41ESSID
    42Network Authentication
    43EAP Type
    44Phase 2 Method(Inner Authentication)
    45User Name (WRITE-ONLY)
    46Password (WRITE-ONLY)
    47Pass Phrase (WRITE-ONLY)
    48WEP Data Encryption
    49WEP AP Authentication
    50WEP Key Selected
    51WEP Key 1 (WRITE-ONLY)
    52WEP Key 2 (WRITE-ONLY)
    53WEP Key 3 (WRITE-ONLY)
    54WEP Key 4 (WRITE-ONLY)
    55Show Signal Strength
    56Power Saving Mode
    57Group Cipher
    58Wireless MAC Address
    59Regulatory Domain
    60Radio Physical Mode
    61Minimum Active Channel Dwell Time
    62Maximum Active Channel Dwell Time
    63Active Scanning Radio Channel
    64Hexadecimal Pass Phrase (64 hexadecimal digits, WRITE-ONLY)
    65Use Haxadecimal PSK
    66WiFi Testing Mode
    67Use Client Certificate
    68Signal Strength ( ~RSSI - READ ONLY)
    69SSL Port
    70DHCP Host Name ( DHCP Option 12 - READ ONLY)
    72WiFi Enable
    See Also:

    • Constructor Detail

      • NetworkWirelessSettings_DPL

        public NetworkWirelessSettings_DPL(ConnectionBase conn)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState_DPL.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        conn - connection to printer
